                                                  written lines: 25; The beginning of each pericope is marked in the margin by a large ornamental ס. Each pericope is divided into 7 sections numbered with Hebrew letters in colours in the margin. The numbers of the commandments are written in red ink in the margins. The masorah magna occupies two lines in the upper and three lines in the lower margin.
